CSS
    Cascading style sheet
    a layer on top of html

inline css
    we can use inline css by adding style 
    attribute to the element we want to add style
    eg: <p style="color:red;"></p>

internal css
    we write internal css using <style> tag 
    style tag is defined under header tag
    Syntax
        <style>
            selector{property:value; p2:value2;}
        </style>

        we can target or select an element
        by writing the element name eg: h1, p div
        or by using the class name
        class names are case sensitive 